		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-sophisticatedjanedoe bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent highlander-comment" id="comment-356091">
				<div id="div-comment-356091" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1e43ad5d975e99e33afc8969d838c688?s=40&#038;d=wavatar&#038;r=R' class='avatar avatar-40' height='40' width='40' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://fightcopyrighttrolls.wordpress.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>SJD</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://fightcopyrighttrolls.com/2014/04/06/due-to-lack-of-evidence-copyright-trolls-resort-to-polygraph-tests/comment-page-1/#comment-356091">
			April 8, 2014 at 00:11</a>		</div>

		<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_4632577_comm_356091"></div><blockquote><p>Hardship is when a defendant may be liable for the conduct, but has extenuating circumstances where Plaintiff does not wish to proceed against him or her. Examples are when a defendant has little or no assets, defendant has serious illness or <b>has recently deceased</b>, defendant is currently active duty US military, defendant is a charitable organization or school, etc. </p></blockquote>
<p>The key word here is &#8220;recently&#8221;: only <i>recently</i> deceased are off the hook; those who are dead for a long time — no such luck!</p>

		<div class="reply">
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2014/04/06/due-to-lack-of-evidence-copyright-trolls-resort-to-polygraph-tests/?replytocom=356091#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-356091", "356091", "respond", "8431")'>Reply</a>		</div>
