		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://fightcopyrighttrolls.com/2014/04/06/due-to-lack-of-evidence-copyright-trolls-resort-to-polygraph-tests/comment-page-1/#comment-362169">
			April 13, 2014 at 14:49</a>		</div>

		<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_4632577_comm_362169"></div><p>Which is why I tell EVERYONE to first disable WPS, then disable SSID broadcast, then set up MAC filtering with a whitelist.  I installed DD-WRT on an old Linksys and turned it into a wireless bridge for my old Blu-ray player, then while I was screwing with the settings (remotely) I accidentally blacklisted everything heh.  Never got around to hard wiring it and removing the MAC filter.</p>

